  "name": "CMO VWMA Momentum Trader",
  "description": "This algorithm utilizes the Chande Momentum Oscillator (CMO) to identify strong upward momentum by generating buy signals when the CMO crosses above +50 and the price closes above the Volume Weighted Moving Average (VWMA). Conversely, sell signals are triggered when the CMO indicates a downward trend, ensuring timely entries and exits in the market.",
  "algorithm_type": "Momentum",
  "prompt": "Create an expert-level momentum trading algorithm using Python that operates on 15-minute bars. Use the Chande Momentum Oscillator (CMO) with a 14-period length combined with the Volume Weighted Moving Average (VWMA) over 20 periods. Generate a buy signal when the CMO crosses above +50 and price closes above the VWMA, confirming strong upward momentum. Generate a sell signal when the CMO crosses below -50 and price closes below the VWMA, indicating strong downward momentum. Implement a trailing stop based on 1.5 times the 14-period Average True Range (ATR) to exit trades, and include a rule to avoid entering trades during volume below the 20-period VWMA volume average to filter weak participation. Provide clear entry, exit, and stop-loss logic with position sizing based on a fixed percentage of account equity.",
